The best thing about the photo booth may be the feeling of spontaneity. There is no photographer suggesting how to smile, how to stand, or that your smile must be more 'genuine'. From the time the wedding guest pushes the touchscreen monitor until the four photos happen to be taken, probably the most crazy, fun, and humourous things might be captured onto film.

We also get to see the purest feelings of affection displayed within the photos: a group of friends, packing themselves in to the photo booth to create the silliest faces possible. an elderly couple - perhaps the grandparents of the groom? - sneaking in to the photo booth for their millionth kiss together. and also the bride and groom themselves, bride in groom's arms, for just one of their first kisses together as husband and wife.

Unleash the party and unleash the love with your own wedding photobooth!